title: October Story
description: A chance human interest interview reveals a girl has created a working television that would cost only a few dollars. NBC executives become interested, and a young man is assigned to help her complete plans at her home.

title: The Copper
description: A wimpy, accident-prone little man aspires to marry a tough police sergeant's daughter, and becomes a rookie cop. He's given an undercover assignment, posing as a convict in a prison to gain information on his cell mates.

title: Her Prince Charming
description: A lonely old woman who spends all her time going to radio and TV quiz shows wins a weekend as the guest of a old time movie star.

title: John Turner
description: A childless couple befriend a boy who has been deserted by his aunt and uncle.

title: Moment of Panic
description: A man is tortured by guilt after failing to report a hit-and-run accident.

title: The Huntress
description: A working girl takes her life savings to Las Vegas in search of a rich husband.

title: Suitable for Framing
description: A high-pressure public relations man takes a job as a publicist for a new art gallery. But the gallery owner has his own plans for hitting the front pages, far more artful than the publicist could suggest.

title: Dear Harriet Heart-Throb
description: A bachelor journalist writes an advice to the lovelorn column.

title: Flight Report
description: Walter Matthau plays the role of Lieutenant Burch in a drama about Naval carrier pilots during World War II.

title: Doing Her Bit
description: Coomedy about a movie star's visit to troops in Korea.

title: The Rabbit Trap
description: "While on vacation, a father and son set a rabbit trap. They are to return the next day to free the rabbit, a prospective pet for the boy. But the family is forced to return to the city after a rush call from the father's demanding boss."--TV guide, February 13, 1955.

title: Backfire
description: A sociology professor who believes people have no real choices in their destinies must rethink his principles when he witnesses a crime.

title: Beloved Stranger
description: No fewer than three women could be the 'beloved stranger'. One of these three persons is to inherit the possessions from a sea captain. Unfortunately, the captain has died at sea without having the time to name which of the three women was the elect. It is up to a lawyer to investigate and find her.

title: In the Days of Our Youth
Grow Up
description: A 16-year-old boy finds that advice from friends, family, and teachers is no substitute for winning the battle for maturity by himself.

title: Weekend in Vermont
description: Grace Barre takes her New York fiancé home to Vermont to meet her family, anticipating a cool reception.

title: The Dark Side of the Moon
